cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the problem of finding the largest and smallest area triangles on a set of imprecise points modeled as parallel line segments. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for solving the problem, as well as discrete mathematics (cs.DM) for analyzing the complexity of the algorithms. The problem of finding the smallest largest-area triangle is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
